{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a49617aa-1519-4332-bd10-9dd9371a07d2","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"DisplayName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"54eedb4a-c149-4b94-8eda-2179bba10a2e","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"7C26:D4E0A:28EB7CE:2D66AE1:69F94BF2"},"id":"79ad5e21-3894-4ada-93e6-c3e9e46b040f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:46:33.296Z","parentId":"687ae9fd-94fc-4438-926a-c8f5a86d9205"}
